item.description:
Say if I need to compute the sum of a series like this one:
\begin{equation} y = 1 + 2 x + 3 x^2 + 4 x^3 + \dots \ , \label{eq:a} \end{equation}
where $|x| &lt; 1$. This series looks like a geometric series in which case the sum can be computed from

For a radial profile of \(I( r)\), the enclosed flux within the radius \(r\) is given by
\begin{equation*} F( r) = \int_{0}^{2 \pi} d\phi \int_{0}^{r} dr r I(r, \phi) \ . \end{equation*}
I&rsquo;m only concerned about azimuthal symmetric cases, so \(F( r) = 2\pi \int_{0}^{r} dr r I( r)\) .
